Amen brother

>>63665189
I am entirely here for romance. That is best achieved with a complex story. However, they are more difficult than short stories, due to the tendency of the writer to go into filler territory or writing themselves in a corner. If you are to attempt a complex story, always ask yourself if a scene is serving a purpose. A good measure is if you are rereading your story and you start glossing over a part. That's a clue that your section is a little boring. You can add intrigue by asking a question first thing in a scene and then answering it later. There should be suspense in every fiber of the story, until the climax.
